reviews.review:
While it was a great ending to the Skywalker Saga, it left me wanting more!! 
I also wish they would have go into some detail as to how Palpatine survived Return of the Jedi.  Overall I enjoyed it but also wish the saga would keep going, there's plenty more story for the remaining characters that I would like to see brought to the big screen.

Well... what to say... 

I dive deeper into the SW universe than most, I am invested more than 99% of the planet. 
It was a great movie, full stop.

I will come back here in a few weeks or months and edit my review, but Abrams, who I thought made a mockery of Ep7, maybe...just actually set up a plotline that might be one for the ages.

Go watch, I'll fill the rest out later
Thought it was awesome definitely fun to watch .

I disagree with most of the criticism of this movie. This was the Star Wars-iest Star Wars since Return of the Jedi. Very good movie, great character arc closure for originals, and the most interesting story lines yet for the newbies. It was an impossible film to make and I think they did a great job. Definitely best of the new trilogy.
A Great conclusion, on to the next saga!

As a life-long Star Wars fan, this movie represents an emotional capstone to 42 years of the Skywalker Saga. Though I am sad that it is over, all stories/sagas/adventures must come to an end. I am lucky to have been alive to see the entire Skywalker Saga.
Didn't knew Micheal Bay was the director, how cool !!

I think that there were some unnecessary scenes in the film and some that could have been executed differently. But overall I enjoyed this film. The action and special effects were great and I liked that they brought back some old characters . I think the ending could have been better but overall, it was an entertaining finish to the Skywalker Saga.
It was fast paced, fun, and enjoyable. Lots of questions get answered, but new ones also arise. Overall, was a great ride and can't wait to go see it again in 3D over Christmas!
